WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:05.460
♪♪

00:05.460 --> 00:07.500
[ Gasps ] Yes!

00:07.500 --> 00:09.040
I got the highest score
in the class

00:09.040 --> 00:11.290
so I get to pick the movie
for "Feature Friday."

00:11.290 --> 00:12.830
Congratulations,
Sweetheart.

00:12.830 --> 00:14.790
You studied so hard
for that vocabulary test

00:14.790 --> 00:17.000
and it paid off.

00:17.000 --> 00:19.000
Franklin, we'll need
to brainstorm

00:19.000 --> 00:20.710
movie options
during recess.

00:20.710 --> 00:24.170
Okay, but the only movie
I've ever seen is "Soapdish."

00:24.170 --> 00:27.290
Katie: Uch. Tara, Sage,
Jennifer, and Holly.

00:27.290 --> 00:30.000
It's like if The Beatles
were made up entirely of Yokos.

00:30.000 --> 00:31.710
Look at what
she's wearing.

00:31.710 --> 00:34.000
She's not even wearing
a bra.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.040
Who cares if I'm not wearing
a --

00:38.330 --> 00:40.330
I'll have
you plant-based idiots know

00:40.330 --> 00:41.830
that I am wearing a bra
today.

00:41.830 --> 00:43.580
This is just as high
as they go now.

00:43.580 --> 00:46.880
It's brave of you to share
something so sad,

00:46.880 --> 00:48.460
but we weren't
talking about you.

00:48.460 --> 00:50.500
Who else would you be insulting
if not me?

00:50.500 --> 00:52.330
Her.

00:52.330 --> 00:57.880
♪♪

00:57.880 --> 01:00.210
How does she have wind blowing
gently through her hair?

01:00.210 --> 01:01.920
We're in an enclosed space.

01:01.920 --> 01:03.460
Who cares
about her hair?

01:03.460 --> 01:05.580
Check out
all that...cleave.

01:05.580 --> 01:06.580
Yowza.

01:06.580 --> 01:07.580
Who is she?

01:07.580 --> 01:09.330
Harper the home wrecker.

01:09.330 --> 01:12.250
She's Insignia Vaillancourt's
new step-mom.

01:12.250 --> 01:13.880
Not a name.
That's not a name.

01:13.880 --> 01:15.620
She busted up Claude
and Michelle's marriage

01:15.620 --> 01:17.250
and now she's prancing
around Westport

01:17.250 --> 01:18.420
smiling at people,

01:18.420 --> 01:20.170
volunteering
at the animal shelter.

01:20.170 --> 01:21.920
It's disgusting.
[ Muttering ]

01:21.920 --> 01:24.790
There's finally someone
they hate more than me.

01:24.790 --> 01:26.620
Harper obviously married
for money.

01:26.620 --> 01:27.380
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

01:27.380 --> 01:28.580
But you sure didn't.

01:28.580 --> 01:30.290
[ Laughter ]

01:30.290 --> 01:33.290
Okay, maybe she's just someone
they hate as much as me.

01:36.750 --> 01:40.750
♪♪

01:40.750 --> 01:44.540
I love seeing the Westport moms
freak out about Harper.

01:44.540 --> 01:46.120
Nothing scares
those be-yatches

01:46.120 --> 01:48.170
like a trophy wife
blowing into town.

01:48.170 --> 01:49.420
They think their husbands
will trade them in

01:49.420 --> 01:50.460
for a younger model, too.

01:50.460 --> 01:51.920
That is so sad.

01:51.920 --> 01:53.120
[ Laughs ]
It is funny.

01:53.120 --> 01:55.330
[ Laughs ]

01:55.330 --> 01:57.170
Oh, d-did you say sad?

01:57.170 --> 01:58.500
Since I moved to this town,

01:58.500 --> 02:01.460
these women have dedicated
their lives to judging me

02:01.460 --> 02:03.330
and making me feel like
an outcast.

02:03.330 --> 02:06.290
They make fun of your clothes,
your hair, your makeup,

02:06.290 --> 02:08.120
the sound
of your pleather wallet

02:08.120 --> 02:10.000
sliding out
of your pleather bag.

02:10.000 --> 02:13.170
Sicking Harper on them is
my chance for a little payback.

02:13.170 --> 02:15.500
Mm-hmm. Make them feel
like they make you feel.

02:15.500 --> 02:17.500
You two aren't worried
about Greg or Richard

02:17.500 --> 02:19.210
getting any ideas
about trading you in?

02:19.210 --> 02:20.710
Greg would never cheat
on me.

02:20.710 --> 02:22.210
Fool loves me too much.
[ Chuckling ]

02:22.210 --> 02:23.790
And Richard has a healthy fear
of diseases.

02:23.790 --> 02:25.580
Mm.
Oh, thank God
for those herpes commercials

02:25.580 --> 02:26.620
during "NCIS."

02:26.620 --> 02:28.540
Ohh, hey, look.

02:28.540 --> 02:29.920
Let's start messing with them
right now.

02:29.920 --> 02:31.250
Ask me how I look
so young for my age.

02:31.250 --> 02:32.620
Ask me loudly.

02:32.620 --> 02:35.750
[ Loudly ] Angela,
you look so young for your age.

02:35.750 --> 02:37.170
What's your secret?

02:37.170 --> 02:38.750
[ Loudly ]
Oh, you wouldn't believe me.

02:38.750 --> 02:39.920
Baby pee.

02:39.920 --> 02:42.080
An infant's urine
is better than BOTOX.

02:42.080 --> 02:43.380
I mean,
that's just science.

02:43.380 --> 02:46.120
Science?
Isn't that what doctors use?

02:46.120 --> 02:48.620
Sure is.
Just take a wet diaper

02:48.620 --> 02:50.880
and rub it
all over your face

02:50.880 --> 02:52.580
twice a night,
five to ten minutes.

02:52.580 --> 02:53.920
[ Laughter ]

02:53.920 --> 02:55.670
I mean,
for a fifty-five year old woman

02:55.670 --> 02:57.170
you look fantastic!

02:57.170 --> 02:58.710
[ Laughter ]

02:58.710 --> 03:00.170
[ Quietly ] Do you think
that they're going for it?

03:00.170 --> 03:01.330
[ Quietly ]
Just to be sure...

03:01.330 --> 03:04.000
[ Loudly ] Oh, my --
You're sixty-five?!

03:04.000 --> 03:05.420
Ow!

03:05.420 --> 03:06.620
[ Normal voice ]
Grandma took her Geritol.

03:06.620 --> 03:07.880
[ Laughter ]

03:07.880 --> 03:09.960
♪♪

03:09.960 --> 03:13.040
I have to pick the perfect movie
for "Feature Friday."

03:13.040 --> 03:15.380
Okay, so which one
of these movies

03:15.380 --> 03:17.330
do you think
most represents me --

03:17.330 --> 03:19.540
"Matilda,"
"The Sound of Music" --

03:19.540 --> 03:21.830
Ooo, "The Sound of Music."

03:21.830 --> 03:25.170
I once had a layover in Miami
with Christopher Plummer.

03:25.170 --> 03:26.120
Mm.

03:26.120 --> 03:27.620
He made my hills
come alive.

03:27.620 --> 03:29.880
[ Chuckles ]

03:29.880 --> 03:31.330
That one's
coming off the list.

03:34.960 --> 03:36.710
Did you ever notice your mom
makes everything about herself?

03:36.710 --> 03:38.420
No, Greg.
I've never met my mom.

03:38.420 --> 03:40.540
Well, I've had enough.
She's living here now,

03:40.540 --> 03:42.330
she needs to take an interest
in our lives.

03:42.330 --> 03:44.120
She knows your name
and where we keep the vermouth.

03:44.120 --> 03:46.250
That's as interested
as she gets.

03:46.250 --> 03:47.880
Where are you going?
There's a new mom
at school

03:47.880 --> 03:49.460
and I'm going
to go welcome her

03:49.460 --> 03:50.880
and encourage her
to get involved.

03:50.880 --> 03:51.710
Oh, that's nice of you.

03:51.710 --> 03:52.960
Uh-huh.

03:52.960 --> 03:53.960
What's your ulterior motive?

03:53.960 --> 03:55.750
Revenge.
Oh, the usual.

03:58.330 --> 03:59.540
Will you guys help me
get Grandma

03:59.540 --> 04:01.210
to stop thinking about herself
for one minute

04:01.210 --> 04:02.670
and ask a question
about one of us?

04:02.670 --> 04:03.750
Sure,
and while we're at it,

04:03.750 --> 04:05.000
we can get her
to stop telling us

04:05.000 --> 04:07.500
all the old-timey celebrities
she mile-highed with.

04:07.500 --> 04:08.880
That would never happen.

04:08.880 --> 04:10.250
I was being sarcastic.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.920
Well, stop it.
It's confusing.

04:11.920 --> 04:12.880
Come on, guys,
we can do this.

04:12.880 --> 04:13.620
Teamwork.

04:13.620 --> 04:16.500
Gooooooooo...!

04:16.500 --> 04:18.580
I'll-get-you-guys-iTunes-
gift-cards-if-you-help-meeee...!

04:18.580 --> 04:21.290
All: Gooooo Ottos!

04:21.290 --> 04:25.790
♪♪

04:25.790 --> 04:28.170
Hi. I'm Katie Otto.

04:28.170 --> 04:30.500
My daughter Anna-Kat
is in the same class

04:30.500 --> 04:31.750
as your stepdaughter --

04:31.750 --> 04:33.880
Em...blem?

04:33.880 --> 04:35.170
Oh, Insignia.
Mm.

04:35.170 --> 04:37.040
[ Chuckles ]
Emblem isn't a name.

04:37.040 --> 04:39.000
[ Chuckles ]
Of course, I feel so silly.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.830
I made you some cookies.

04:41.830 --> 04:44.380
Aw, that is so sweet.

04:44.380 --> 04:45.250
No one's really
reached out to me

04:45.250 --> 04:46.080
since I moved here.

04:46.080 --> 04:48.000
They just look at me
and whisper.

04:48.000 --> 04:49.960
Harper,
I don't just have cookies.

04:49.960 --> 04:51.540
I have advice.

04:51.540 --> 04:53.080
I was iced out
by the Westport moms

04:53.080 --> 04:54.250
when we first moved here too,

04:54.250 --> 04:56.880
but then I threw
a fantastic Spring Gala

04:56.880 --> 04:58.290
and now everyone loves me.

04:58.290 --> 05:00.080
So, what should I do?

05:00.080 --> 05:02.170
You need to put your stamp
on the school

05:02.170 --> 05:04.120
with a high-profile
volunteer gig.

05:04.120 --> 05:05.920
Do you work?
[ Laughs ]
You're funny.

05:05.920 --> 05:07.330
I like that.

05:07.330 --> 05:08.460
[ Laughs ]

05:08.460 --> 05:10.540
And you need to get to know
all the moms.

05:10.540 --> 05:11.710
And dads, too.

05:11.710 --> 05:13.380
I love that idea.
Mm-hmm.

05:13.380 --> 05:16.080
I always say, "Volunteering
is our soul's way

05:16.080 --> 05:18.420
of animating gratitude
for our blessings."

05:18.420 --> 05:21.250
Monogram is so lucky
to have you as a step-mom.

05:21.250 --> 05:22.960
Insignia.
Her, too.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.420
♪♪

05:25.420 --> 05:28.040
Oof. I had a day
you would not believe.

05:28.040 --> 05:30.040
You know
what I can't believe?

05:30.040 --> 05:31.880
How good I look
in these jeans.

05:31.880 --> 05:33.710
[ Chuckles ] Am I right?

05:33.710 --> 05:35.420
[ Chuckles ]

05:35.420 --> 05:37.500
♪♪

05:37.500 --> 05:39.710
Hey, Grandma,
quick question.

05:39.710 --> 05:41.500
For my tattoo --
do I go full-sleeve

05:41.500 --> 05:43.250
or just a treasure map
on my back?

05:43.250 --> 05:44.670
A tattoo?

05:44.670 --> 05:45.620
[ Chuckles ]

05:45.620 --> 05:47.830
I'll show you a tattoo.

05:47.830 --> 05:48.920
[ Sighs ]

05:48.920 --> 05:50.380
I got this in Dublin.

05:50.380 --> 05:52.500
It's a rainbow
with a pot of gold at the end.

05:52.500 --> 05:53.880
I don't see a pot of gold.

05:53.880 --> 05:55.000
Oh, well,
that part's hidden.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.210
♪♪

05:59.210 --> 06:02.330
[ Crying ]

06:02.330 --> 06:04.420
Shhhh.

06:07.040 --> 06:08.290
[ Crying ]

06:08.290 --> 06:09.620
Shhh!

06:09.620 --> 06:16.830
♪♪

06:16.830 --> 06:18.920
Holly: Hey, Katie.

06:18.920 --> 06:23.120
Holly. Jennifer, Sage --
Darth Vegan.

06:23.120 --> 06:24.880
Man,
what smells like --

06:24.880 --> 06:26.580
Baby pee!
They're doing it!

06:26.580 --> 06:27.880
These idiots are doing it!

06:27.880 --> 06:30.000
You all look so great!

06:30.000 --> 06:32.920
You really must be
pampering yourselves.

06:32.920 --> 06:35.000
I gotta remember to tell that
to Doris and Angela.

06:35.000 --> 06:36.880
Good morning.
This is Harper

06:36.880 --> 06:38.580
and she's volunteered
to be room mom

06:38.580 --> 06:40.920
for Mr. Lombardo's class.

06:40.920 --> 06:42.920
Oh, the room mom has to have
a ton of interaction

06:42.920 --> 06:44.210
with us parents
so I think we need someone

06:44.210 --> 06:45.250
who knows their way around
more.

06:45.250 --> 06:47.290
But thanks!
[ Chuckling ]

06:47.290 --> 06:48.580
That's why Harper
wanted the job.

06:48.580 --> 06:50.120
To get to know
the parents better.

06:50.120 --> 06:51.380
I think
it's a capital idea.

06:51.380 --> 06:52.750
Aww, thanks,
Principal Ablin.

06:52.750 --> 06:54.330
She knows my name.

06:54.330 --> 06:55.170
[ Chuckles ]

06:55.170 --> 06:56.420
And thank you, Katie.

06:56.420 --> 06:58.210
I never would
have volunteered for room mom

06:58.210 --> 07:00.210
if it wasn't
for your guidance.

07:00.210 --> 07:02.330
I can't wait to spend
a lot of time

07:02.330 --> 07:04.540
with all
you amazing moms.

07:06.500 --> 07:07.710
And your husbands!

07:14.540 --> 07:15.880
♪♪

07:15.880 --> 07:18.080
After careful consideration,

07:18.080 --> 07:20.460
I have chosen my movie
for "Feature Friday."

07:20.460 --> 07:24.500
Franklin,
the envelope, please?

07:24.500 --> 07:26.790
This is a clipboard.

07:26.790 --> 07:28.830
I told you to grab
an envelope.

07:28.830 --> 07:30.880
My mom said
I can't use envelopes anymore.

07:30.880 --> 07:32.380
I like the taste of the glue
too much.

07:32.380 --> 07:33.670
Oh, Franklin.

07:33.670 --> 07:37.000
If you didn't have
those Ed Sheeran good looks.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.920
And the winner is...

07:38.920 --> 07:40.380
Please be "Soapdish."
Please be "Soapdish."

07:40.380 --> 07:41.380
Please be "Soapdish."

07:41.380 --> 07:43.250
"The Goonies"!
[ Groans, stomps ]

07:43.250 --> 07:45.420
Perfect movie! The fat kid
was named Chunk,

07:45.420 --> 07:47.380
the slow guy
was named Sloth.

07:47.380 --> 07:48.620
Oh, it was back
when you could just call 'em

07:48.620 --> 07:49.880
like you saw 'em.

07:49.880 --> 07:51.250
[ Chuckles ]

07:51.250 --> 07:53.210
Are you reading
a school email?

07:53.210 --> 07:55.250
I thought you said we were
forbidden from doing that.

07:55.250 --> 07:56.250
Mnh-mnh,
it's from Harper.

07:56.250 --> 07:58.250
She's calling
a mandatory parent meeting

07:58.250 --> 08:00.330
of "The Feelings Council"
tomorrow.

08:00.330 --> 08:02.420
What's that?
No idea.

08:02.420 --> 08:04.000
But those Westport dopes
will be there feeling bad

08:04.000 --> 08:05.580
about themselves,
so I'm in.

08:05.580 --> 08:07.080
You're a mom,
you have a job --

08:07.080 --> 08:09.210
is undermining their marriages
the best use of your time?

08:09.210 --> 08:11.210
You make time for things
that are important, Greg.

08:11.210 --> 08:15.750
♪♪

08:15.750 --> 08:16.790
You're first, Grandma.
Pick a card

08:16.790 --> 08:18.330
and ask me a question.

08:18.330 --> 08:20.830
Well, this seems silly,
but okay.

08:22.620 --> 08:25.040
If you could have dinner
with anyone, dead or alive,

08:25.040 --> 08:26.380
who would it be?

08:26.380 --> 08:28.120
-Well --
-Marilyn Monroe.

08:28.120 --> 08:30.170
No, I'm supposed to --
She had
an intimate relationship

08:30.170 --> 08:32.290
with some of the most powerful
men in America.

08:32.290 --> 08:33.290
[ Chuckles ] And plus,

08:33.290 --> 08:35.330
I'd love to compare notes
on Brando.

08:35.330 --> 08:37.290
No, Kathryn,
the other person --
Next question!

08:37.290 --> 08:40.330
Oh.
Well, easy: flight.

08:40.330 --> 08:42.170
Why would I waste a superpower
on invisible

08:42.170 --> 08:43.420
when I look like this?

08:43.420 --> 08:45.210
[ Chuckles ]

08:45.210 --> 08:46.540
Bury the body
in the desert,

08:46.540 --> 08:48.380
burn the car,
head for Rosarito.

08:48.380 --> 08:50.330
That's what you would do
if someone asked you

08:50.330 --> 08:51.500
to go Dutch
on the first date?

08:51.500 --> 08:53.120
Yeah.

08:53.120 --> 08:55.120
How is this even
a question?

08:55.120 --> 08:56.710
I'd save myself
and let the school bus

08:56.710 --> 08:57.750
go over the cliff.

08:57.750 --> 08:59.210
[ Chuckles ]

08:59.210 --> 09:01.170
You're right,
this really is fun.

09:01.170 --> 09:04.210
♪♪

09:04.210 --> 09:06.830
Feelings Council
is an ancient ritual,

09:06.830 --> 09:08.210
born at Coachella Fest,

09:08.210 --> 09:10.290
to create
an inclusive space

09:10.290 --> 09:14.120
through community, mindfulness,
and gratitude.

09:14.120 --> 09:15.380
Isn't she fun?

09:15.380 --> 09:17.080
She's so free and open.

09:17.080 --> 09:18.750
Every woman her age is.

09:18.750 --> 09:21.830
Tinder is swimming
with Harpers.

09:21.830 --> 09:22.920
Do you want me to send you
the link?

09:22.920 --> 09:23.710
I'm gonna send you
the link.

09:23.710 --> 09:26.170
[ Gong crashes ]

09:26.170 --> 09:28.080
Did you all feel that?

09:28.080 --> 09:30.290
We just raised
our universal vibration.

09:30.290 --> 09:31.960
[ Chuckles ]
Did you feel that, honey?

09:31.960 --> 09:33.250
Oh, I felt it.

09:33.250 --> 09:34.670
I so felt it.

09:34.670 --> 09:36.460
I felt it, too.

09:36.460 --> 09:39.540
Sweetie, someone asked me
the other day if I was bulimic.

09:39.540 --> 09:40.380
[ Chuckles ]

09:40.380 --> 09:41.620
The Class Council
must start

09:41.620 --> 09:43.670
with our opening rituals --

09:43.670 --> 09:44.830
The gong,

09:44.830 --> 09:47.170
an offering of water
for our ancestors...

09:47.170 --> 09:50.290
and a talking stick.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.670
Now, in council,

09:51.670 --> 09:56.620
only the being holding
the talking stick may speak.

09:56.620 --> 09:59.330
She kind of makes you feel
old and ugly, doesn't she?

09:59.330 --> 10:00.620
Not the universal you.

10:00.620 --> 10:02.120
You, in particular.

10:02.120 --> 10:03.710
You're gonna pay
for this,

10:03.710 --> 10:05.380
and I know you can't afford it
because you're a stupid poor.

10:05.380 --> 10:06.120
[ Gasps ]

10:06.120 --> 10:07.460
Uh-uh-uh.

10:07.460 --> 10:09.000
And like I tell
my husband's first wife,

10:09.000 --> 10:10.170
let's not name call.

10:10.170 --> 10:11.380
[ Sighs ]

10:11.380 --> 10:13.960
I know some of my ideas
may seem strange

10:13.960 --> 10:16.040
because I'm from
a much younger generation.

10:16.040 --> 10:17.880
[ Chuckles ]
No you're not,

10:17.880 --> 10:18.920
what year were you born?

10:18.920 --> 10:20.460
1993.
How about you?

10:20.460 --> 10:21.330
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

10:21.330 --> 10:23.580
I was born t--

10:23.580 --> 10:25.000
[ Laughing ] Can't talk
without the talking stick.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.620
So...

10:26.620 --> 10:29.790
Harper, you are just
so wonderful.

10:29.790 --> 10:32.040
I wish that there were
more women from your generation

10:32.040 --> 10:33.710
coming into our community.

10:33.710 --> 10:34.830
Hear, hear.

10:34.830 --> 10:35.880
Oh.

10:39.670 --> 10:42.460
So, Claude, how did you meet
the true love of your life

10:42.460 --> 10:44.880
who rekindled your manhood
and made you realize

10:44.880 --> 10:48.080
that your first marriage
was a mistake?

10:48.080 --> 10:50.710
Uh, my first wife,
um...

10:50.710 --> 10:52.120
[ Chuckles ]

10:52.120 --> 10:53.830
Uh...
Michele.

10:53.830 --> 10:55.330
Her name is Michele.

10:55.330 --> 10:56.330
Talking stick.

10:56.330 --> 10:57.830
Talking stick you!

10:57.830 --> 11:00.000
Michele wanted me to get
into yoga,

11:00.000 --> 11:04.620
and Harper was the instructor
for our introductory class.

11:04.620 --> 11:07.790
You always said yoga would be
great for my lower back.

11:07.790 --> 11:09.790
So where do you teach?
I would love to keep --

11:09.790 --> 11:12.250
Honey,
you're hogging the stick.

11:12.250 --> 11:14.170
Here's a great yoga stretch.

11:14.170 --> 11:15.750
Okay.

11:15.750 --> 11:18.540
[ Exhales deeply ]

11:18.540 --> 11:19.750
[ Moaning ] Oh, yeah.

11:19.750 --> 11:21.670
Okay, yeah.

11:21.670 --> 11:23.710
Right there.

11:23.710 --> 11:25.750
[ Sighs ]

11:25.750 --> 11:26.790
[ Sighs ]

11:28.620 --> 11:31.960
Feels good to get involved
in school.

11:31.960 --> 11:33.460
Katie:
It was a huge success

11:33.460 --> 11:36.170
even though she banned clapping
in the classroom.

11:36.170 --> 11:37.420
She did away
with clapping?

11:37.420 --> 11:39.710
Yep. So now if we agree
on something

11:39.710 --> 11:40.880
and want to show
our appreciation,

11:40.880 --> 11:42.460
we have to do this --

11:42.460 --> 11:45.210
[ Blowing ]
Why?

11:45.210 --> 11:47.790
So no one feels less appreciated
than another person.

11:47.790 --> 11:49.290
And then you lunged
at her.

11:49.290 --> 11:50.710
How many people did it take
to pull you off?

11:50.710 --> 11:52.000
Did they have to call in
the gym teachers?

11:52.000 --> 11:53.710
No, I kept it together

11:53.710 --> 11:56.830
because the Witches of Westport
feel so bad about themselves.

11:56.830 --> 11:58.670
It was really beautiful.

11:58.670 --> 12:01.420
They're going insane
trying to out-Harper Harper.

12:01.420 --> 12:04.710
♪♪

12:04.710 --> 12:06.500
[ Machine buzzes ]

12:06.500 --> 12:09.330
♪♪

12:09.330 --> 12:11.620
[ Tearing, screaming ]

12:11.620 --> 12:13.620
[ Panting ]

12:13.620 --> 12:23.120
♪♪

12:23.120 --> 12:27.040
[ All groaning ]

12:27.040 --> 12:29.170
As long as they're unhappy,
I'm happy.

12:29.170 --> 12:31.290
Oh God.
That sounds terrible.

12:31.290 --> 12:32.710
Am I terrible?

12:32.710 --> 12:33.830
No.

12:33.830 --> 12:34.960
I'm good.

12:34.960 --> 12:36.040
I'm perfect.

12:39.580 --> 12:42.250
Anna-Kat, what's wrong?

12:42.250 --> 12:45.210
Insignia's mom said
I can't show my movie in class.

12:45.210 --> 12:47.290
Harper? Why would she ban
"The Goonies"?!

12:47.290 --> 12:48.500
It's the perfect movie.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.420
She said
that it's inappropriate

12:50.420 --> 12:52.830
and that I need to meditate
on why I'd choose something

12:52.830 --> 12:55.000
that doesn't represent
my best self.

12:55.000 --> 12:57.500
She probably didn't realize
that you're my daughter.

12:57.500 --> 12:59.120
I'll email her
and straighten it out.

12:59.120 --> 13:00.790
Thanks, Mama.

13:00.790 --> 13:02.080
[ Sighs ] For once
there's someone at the school

13:02.080 --> 13:03.420
that doesn't hate me.

13:03.420 --> 13:04.120
What about the lady
at the front desk?

13:04.120 --> 13:05.380
She likes you.
I was discussing

13:05.380 --> 13:07.330
the other idiot who works
the front desk with her,

13:07.330 --> 13:09.040
and then I just realized
she changed her hair.

13:10.000 --> 13:13.380
I'm sure you now see
why "The Goonies"

13:13.380 --> 13:15.170
is so important
to Anna-Kat.

13:15.170 --> 13:16.880
XO, Katie.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.080
[ Whoosh ]

13:18.080 --> 13:19.380
Sent.

13:19.380 --> 13:20.790
I think it's a nice mix
of "sweet"

13:20.790 --> 13:22.330
and "don't cross me."

13:22.330 --> 13:24.290
Aw, that's how I first
described you to my parents.

13:24.290 --> 13:26.620
[ Computer chimes ]
She replied already.

13:26.620 --> 13:28.460
Harper: Dear Katie, your fire
for your daughter

13:28.460 --> 13:29.420
is inspiring --

13:29.420 --> 13:30.670
Blah, Blah, Blah...

13:30.670 --> 13:32.420
"The Goonies"
promotes lying, greed

13:32.420 --> 13:34.460
and a troubling
pro-pirate agenda.

13:34.460 --> 13:35.960
My inner-voice tells me

13:35.960 --> 13:38.670
Anna-Kat clearly needs
my guidance and influence.

13:38.670 --> 13:40.120
Inner voice?

13:40.120 --> 13:42.380
Katie: What kind of weirdo
has an inner voice?

13:42.380 --> 13:43.920
Uh-oh.

13:43.920 --> 13:45.880
Harper: For good measure,
I've looped in Principal Ablin.

13:45.880 --> 13:47.120
Love and Light.

13:47.120 --> 13:49.210
Looping in Ablin?
Don't loop in --

13:49.210 --> 13:51.040
[ Computer chimes ]
Principal Ablin: Ahoy, Maties!

13:51.040 --> 13:52.290
Though I've never seen
"The Goonies,"

13:52.290 --> 13:53.960
I totally trust
Harper's judgment.

13:53.960 --> 13:54.830
Smiley face emoji.

13:54.830 --> 13:56.290
Prayer hands emoji.

13:56.290 --> 14:00.380
Principal Ablin
AKA "King Of School."

14:00.380 --> 14:03.460
Anna-Kat put hours
into picking her movie.

14:03.460 --> 14:05.620
Also,
this is a parent issue,

14:05.620 --> 14:08.620
so let's keep it
between us.

14:08.620 --> 14:10.000
[ Whoosh, computer chimes ]

14:10.000 --> 14:11.670
Harper: Dear Katie,
perhaps you're right.

14:11.670 --> 14:12.920
Damn right I'm right!

14:12.920 --> 14:14.290
I've looped
in all the parents.

14:14.290 --> 14:15.920
Let's put it
to the hive mind

14:15.920 --> 14:17.500
and make it
a community decision.
[ Groans ]

14:17.500 --> 14:19.170
Community decision?
That's not gonna go your way.

14:19.170 --> 14:20.580
[ Computer chiming ]

14:20.580 --> 14:22.250
-Great call, Harper!
-Totally agree.

14:22.250 --> 14:24.080
Tara: I vote for anything
against Katie Otto.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.830
Middle finger emoji.

14:25.830 --> 14:27.120
Greg?

14:27.120 --> 14:28.920
My screaming pillow,
please.

14:31.330 --> 14:34.000
[ Muffled scream ]

14:34.000 --> 14:35.290
Thank you.
[ Computer chimes ]

14:35.290 --> 14:37.460
Harper: Community,
your feelings are felt.

14:37.460 --> 14:39.290
"The Goonies"
will not be shown.

14:39.290 --> 14:40.380
Seems like the hot monster
you created

14:40.380 --> 14:42.540
has turned the villagers
against you.

14:42.540 --> 14:45.540
As a member
of this "community,"

14:45.540 --> 14:49.210
I'm invoking my sacred right
to call a gathering

14:49.210 --> 14:51.120
of the Feelings Council.

14:51.120 --> 14:53.250
Tomorrow.
During recess.

14:53.250 --> 14:55.500
Be there!
[ Whoosh, computer chimes ]

14:55.500 --> 14:57.040
Bruce: I'll be there.
And Harper,

14:57.040 --> 14:58.960
I'm just circling back to get
the info on your yoga studio.

14:58.960 --> 14:59.880
[ Computer chimes ]

14:59.880 --> 15:01.750
Tara: That's okay. We're good!

15:05.620 --> 15:08.170
♪♪

15:08.170 --> 15:10.170
Did you get Harper
to let me show "The Goonies"?

15:10.170 --> 15:12.000
I am going to a meeting about it
this morning

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
and everything
is going to be fine.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.580
You're the best.

15:15.580 --> 15:18.380
Nothing bad could ever happen
to me when you're around.

15:22.670 --> 15:23.710
No pressure there.

15:23.710 --> 15:25.500
[ Groans ]
This is just so hard.

15:25.500 --> 15:27.330
I guess if ruining
people's lives was easy,

15:27.330 --> 15:29.000
everyone would do it.

15:29.000 --> 15:30.380
Now I got to go rally
the size twos

15:30.380 --> 15:32.080
against that size zero.

15:32.080 --> 15:34.330
I'm actually a double zero
in designer clothes

15:34.330 --> 15:36.210
and a child's twelve
at The Gap.

15:38.710 --> 15:40.500
Great job getting through
to her.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.620
Kathryn,
she wasn't talking about you.

15:42.620 --> 15:44.960
Why not?
You only seem to be interested
in yourself.

15:44.960 --> 15:46.250
Well,
what do you want me to do?

15:46.250 --> 15:47.620
Change
my whole personality?

15:47.620 --> 15:48.880
Maybe just try listening.

15:48.880 --> 15:50.210
Or asking the other person
about their day

15:50.210 --> 15:51.420
before you talk
about yours.

15:51.420 --> 15:52.540
Okay.

15:52.540 --> 15:54.420
Uh, how was your day,
Greg?

15:54.420 --> 15:55.710
Oh, thanks for asking, Kathryn.
My day --

15:55.710 --> 15:57.380
[ Cellphone ringing ]
Ah. To be continued.

15:57.380 --> 15:59.120
Hello?

15:59.120 --> 16:00.880
No, no, no. No, now is
a perfect time

16:00.880 --> 16:03.380
to talk about bundling
my Internet and my phone.

16:03.380 --> 16:04.920
Uh-huh.

16:04.920 --> 16:08.420
♪♪

16:08.420 --> 16:11.670
Ladies, I can't afford
this expensive gym,

16:11.670 --> 16:13.710
so I'm on my free tour,
and I ditched the attendant

16:13.710 --> 16:14.710
in the locker room.

16:14.710 --> 16:15.880
This will be quick.

16:15.880 --> 16:17.620
[ Grunting, yelling ]

16:17.620 --> 16:18.960
[ Panting ]

16:18.960 --> 16:19.790
What do you want, Katie?

16:19.790 --> 16:21.040
Yeah, why are you here?

16:21.040 --> 16:23.830
I need you to back me up
at Feelings Council today

16:23.830 --> 16:25.290
about "Feature Friday."

16:25.290 --> 16:26.790
Harper has gone
way too far.

16:26.790 --> 16:28.960
[ Yells ]

16:28.960 --> 16:30.960
So let me get this straight.

16:30.960 --> 16:32.500
Now that Harper
is bothering you,

16:32.500 --> 16:33.880
it's suddenly a problem?

16:33.880 --> 16:35.210
Exactly.

16:35.210 --> 16:36.620
We're not helping you,
Katie.

16:36.620 --> 16:37.920
But you'll be helping
yourselves, too.

16:37.920 --> 16:39.880
Today it's saying no
to "Goonies,"

16:39.880 --> 16:42.540
but what if tomorrow
it's saying no to BOTOX?

16:42.540 --> 16:44.830
Because she wants moms
to have facial expressions.

16:44.830 --> 16:46.120
[ Gasps ]
[ Gasps ]

16:46.120 --> 16:48.330
See? You all sound,
but don't look, surprised.

16:48.330 --> 16:49.710
[ Yells ]

16:49.710 --> 16:51.250
[ Breathes heavily ]

16:51.250 --> 16:52.710
You know, all of our problems
would be solved

16:52.710 --> 16:54.460
if you just got rid of Harper
as room mom.

16:54.460 --> 16:56.330
It's super confusing
when good ideas

16:56.330 --> 16:58.670
come out
of your awful face.

16:58.670 --> 17:02.040
♪♪

17:02.040 --> 17:03.620
Before Katie starts,

17:03.620 --> 17:05.420
I'll be approving all movies
and classroom snacks

17:05.420 --> 17:07.250
from now on,
so just text me.

17:07.250 --> 17:08.960
And if you have
any other questions or ideas,

17:08.960 --> 17:11.210
you can put them
in here...

17:11.210 --> 17:12.540
I call it
a "thought cradle."

17:12.540 --> 17:13.880
Well, I call it a shoe box

17:13.880 --> 17:15.460
that you decorated
like an 8th grader.

17:15.460 --> 17:17.210
So, I called
a Feelings Council --

17:17.210 --> 17:18.420
Okay, you need
the talking stick.

17:18.420 --> 17:20.040
-So give it to me.
-I don't have it.

17:20.040 --> 17:20.920
I didn't call this meeting.

17:20.920 --> 17:22.500
[ Groans ] Fine.

17:24.380 --> 17:26.420
It's really got to be
a stick.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.670
Ugh.

17:29.500 --> 17:30.790
A-ha!

17:30.790 --> 17:32.170
"Beef stick."

17:32.170 --> 17:33.830
How long have you had that
in your purse?

17:33.830 --> 17:35.330
It doesn't matter.

17:35.330 --> 17:38.000
It expires in 2046.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.830
There's nothing wrong
with "The Goonies."

17:40.830 --> 17:43.500
It is a celebration
of friendship, perseverance,

17:43.500 --> 17:46.920
and accepting people
who are different than you.

17:46.920 --> 17:49.210
[ Sighs ] I must stop
this Feelings Council --

17:49.210 --> 17:51.120
No talking
without the talking stick.

17:51.120 --> 17:53.330
It's time
for you to listen.

17:53.330 --> 17:56.960
Because this is our time.

17:56.960 --> 17:59.880
This is our time
in here.

18:01.880 --> 18:03.080
That was a quote
from the movie.

18:03.080 --> 18:04.210
It rallied everyone
together.

18:04.210 --> 18:05.620
I'm kind of doing
the same thing here.

18:05.620 --> 18:07.420
[ Chuckles ]

18:07.420 --> 18:10.420
Anyhow, Harper,
it's time for you to listen.

18:12.540 --> 18:13.880
"I feel" you need

18:13.880 --> 18:17.460
to stop shoving your ideas
down our throats.

18:17.460 --> 18:20.210
"I feel" like your side-cleave
is way more inappropriate

18:20.210 --> 18:21.830
than a delightful
'80s movie classic.

18:21.830 --> 18:25.460
[ Blowing ]

18:25.460 --> 18:29.790
And I feel that
this nonsense is stupid.

18:29.790 --> 18:32.880
[ Applause ]

18:32.880 --> 18:34.460
Okay, I see
what's going on here.

18:34.460 --> 18:35.960
You're all mad
because I'm young

18:35.960 --> 18:37.880
and I produce more collagen
than I know what to do with.

18:37.880 --> 18:39.710
I believe the Council
can call for a vote

18:39.710 --> 18:42.250
of "No Feeling"
and the leader can be removed.

18:42.250 --> 18:43.790
You can't vote me out.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.420
[ Laughing ]
I am Feelings Council.

18:45.420 --> 18:46.460
Bup!

18:46.460 --> 18:48.790
No talking
without the stick.

18:48.790 --> 18:50.540
Okay, you know what?

18:50.540 --> 18:51.670
I lied!

18:51.670 --> 18:53.330
I do have
the talking stick.

18:53.330 --> 18:55.710
[ Sighs ]
When you're a mother, like me,

18:55.710 --> 18:57.250
you need to be very careful
about --

18:57.250 --> 18:58.920
Uh -- Oh!

18:58.920 --> 19:00.250
You have been a mom
for two months!

19:00.250 --> 19:01.790
Stop giving
parenting advice

19:01.790 --> 19:03.960
or I will knock you
all the way back to Coachella.

19:03.960 --> 19:05.540
[ Scoffs ]

19:05.540 --> 19:07.580
I am going to talk
to Principal Ablin

19:07.580 --> 19:10.920
and have Insignia transferred
to the other class.

19:14.210 --> 19:16.330
Ladies, we put aside
our differences

19:16.330 --> 19:17.620
and worked together
to drive away

19:17.620 --> 19:19.040
the supple room mom.

19:19.040 --> 19:21.670
Maybe this is a new beginning
for us.

19:21.670 --> 19:23.920
Yes, maybe it can be.

19:23.920 --> 19:25.000
I agree.

19:25.000 --> 19:26.580
I mean, Katie,
you're awful,

19:26.580 --> 19:27.750
but at least I know
you can't steal my husband.

19:27.750 --> 19:28.790
[ Laughter ]

19:28.790 --> 19:31.460
Tara, that is one
of the nicer insults

19:31.460 --> 19:33.670
you've ever said to me.

19:33.670 --> 19:35.710
What do you say we make
an effort

19:35.710 --> 19:37.670
to turn over a new leaf?

19:37.670 --> 19:39.120
I agree.

19:39.120 --> 19:41.250
Ooh, this could be
so much fun.

19:41.250 --> 19:42.920
We could flip tires
together.

19:42.920 --> 19:45.290
We're doing
a cabbage soup cleanse.

19:45.290 --> 19:46.790
Oh, of course we're gonna
have to find someone else new

19:46.790 --> 19:48.080
to hate.
You can help us pick them.

19:48.080 --> 19:50.750
[ Gasps ]
You can be one of us!

19:50.750 --> 19:52.880
Katie: Oh, God.
The only thing worse

19:52.880 --> 19:55.500
than them not liking me
is them liking me.

19:55.500 --> 19:56.920
Now that we're all besties,

19:56.920 --> 19:58.670
I should tell you guys
we were messing with you

19:58.670 --> 19:59.750
the other day.

19:59.750 --> 20:01.880
Baby pee does nothing
for the skin.

20:01.880 --> 20:03.330
Other than make you
smell like a ball pit

20:03.330 --> 20:04.380
at Chuck E. Cheese.

20:04.380 --> 20:05.620
[ Gasping ]

20:05.620 --> 20:07.040
I can't believe you.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.380
What kind of a person
does that?

20:09.670 --> 20:12.120
I have pee on my face.

20:14.000 --> 20:15.040
We're back
to hating you.

20:16.330 --> 20:18.790
Everyone hates me again.

20:18.790 --> 20:20.120
That feels right.

20:23.540 --> 20:26.330
♪♪

20:26.330 --> 20:27.830
You're the best mom ever.

20:27.830 --> 20:30.000
I've got a mug of wine
to prove it.

20:30.000 --> 20:31.670
Congratulations to you too.

20:31.670 --> 20:34.040
The kids said my mom asked you
how your day was

20:34.040 --> 20:35.920
and she almost stuck around
to hear the answer.

20:35.920 --> 20:37.620
Baby steps.
I'm happy with that.

20:37.620 --> 20:39.330
Ask yourself
whether you are happy

20:39.330 --> 20:41.170
and you cease to be so.

20:41.170 --> 20:42.920
That's a John Stuart Mill quote.
How do you know that?

20:42.920 --> 20:44.500
[ Chuckles ]
Ah.

20:44.500 --> 20:46.880
I read your book.

20:46.880 --> 20:48.170
When did you read
my book?

20:48.170 --> 20:49.540
Over at Spencer's.

20:49.540 --> 20:50.880
I mean, he bought
all those copies,

20:50.880 --> 20:52.790
and you are
my son-in-law.

20:52.790 --> 20:54.960
I just -- I just wanted
to see what you were up to.

20:54.960 --> 20:56.040
Wow!

20:56.040 --> 20:57.540
-Mm-hmm.
-Thank you.

20:57.540 --> 20:59.250
Oh, you know --
you know my favorite part?

20:59.250 --> 21:00.460
I'd love to hear it.

21:00.460 --> 21:02.920
When the UPS man
delivered the books,

21:02.920 --> 21:04.290
he called me

21:04.290 --> 21:06.170
a "better-put-together
Kate Jackson"

21:06.170 --> 21:07.500
from "Charlie's Angels."

21:07.500 --> 21:08.920
[ Chuckles ]

21:08.920 --> 21:10.920
-Baby steps.
-Yeah.
